Look at the Wikipedia page for “Sovereign citizen movement”, it’s both hilarious and terrifying. This type of ideology isn’t very common in Asia but it’s relatively common in North America and Europe where folks are generally obsessed with “liberty” and whatnot.

@alkaffbonaparte It’s actually more concerning than you’re assuming. She isn’t saying that she only recognises her country’s sovereignty (in fact, the CNA report seems to suggest she’s local), but rather she’s saying that she doesn’t recognise *any* country’s sovereignty over her (read about the “sovereign citizen movement”). And I agree with you entirely on the importance of rules; order is the bedrock of a functional society. Ideologies like this lady’s are a dangerous example of what happens when “liberty” is put on a pedestal above all other values. Another terrifying example is the way protestors with guns occupied the Michigan govt in retaliation to public health measures. Compare that to Asian countries where people trust the govt and listen to experts, and you’ll understand why America is suffering while countries like Singapore have coped well with the pandemic.
